Last night @jpmorgan showcased my artwork at its Wealth Management Summit for Latina and Black Women 🫶🏽.

I entered the event as an artist, and stayed as a student feeling represented and understood. Learning strategies to build wealth isn't so common, but “when women do well their communities do well”. 💖🤞🏽

That’s what leaning on your community is for—to take tips, to learn from experts, and to ask questions! #BuildingANewLegacy

The works on view at the third installment of The New Contemporaries spotlight the various modes through which Black, Latinx, Indigenous, and Asian artists define self-authorship in resistance to fetishization, commodification, and appropriation within the mainstream media landscape. Reflecting upon their lived experiences and positionality, the participating artists have been tasked to represent how their practices embody their expression and movement within our nation's evolving political landscape, whether through self-care, protection, spirituality, or protest.

on view currently at @johndoegallery

26.2 miles 🥇💗 when i decided to run the marathon, i thought the biggest reward to gain from this experience was the gift of discipline.

today, i realized that the real reward was the confidence i learned to have in myself and in the universe— no matter what happened out there, i knew i absolutely was going to finish. 

i think everyone should run a marathon at least once in their life, it really is the most beautiful metaphor for life 🖤

thank you @fitandfullbykayla for pacing me the last 3 miles and being such a supportive friend on the course and throughout this journey. thank you @abbyschmidttraining for training me the past 4 months and all the positive reinforcement. and lastly thank you @nikechicago @yas.runs.chi and @infoaboutog for the bib and experience, @lululemon for the support and gear, and @drinkag1 for the recovery help. 🥹🫂💫
